<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="108" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1788,2031]" pageId="9" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1788,1814]" pageId="9" pageNumber="108">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsal-fin X, 14; pectoral-fin rays 16â€“17; gill rakers 9â€“12+21â€“24 (31â€“35 total); circumpeduncular scales 34â€“36; lateral-line scales 67â€“74; scales from dorsal fin to lateral line 9â€“10; scales from the anal-fin origin to lateral line 20â€“23. Caudal fin emarginated; scales ctenoid; maxilla naked; teeth on vomer and palatines; opercle with three flat spines, central spine largest and directed horizontally; cheek, pectoral-fin base and chest scaly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="109" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1788,2031]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,393]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="109" pageId="9" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1932,1958]" pageId="9" pageNumber="108">Description.</emphasis>
Body elongate; body depth less than head length, about 
<quantity box="[1004,1119,1932,1958]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0287" metricValueMax="1.2446" metricValueMin="0.8128" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" unit="in" value="4.05" valueMax="4.9" valueMin="3.2">3.2â€“4.9 in</quantity>
SL; head length 
<quantity box="[1321,1436,1932,1958]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" metricValueMax="9.144" metricValueMin="6.096" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" unit="in" value="3.0" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="2.4">2.4â€“3.6 in</quantity>
SL. Maxilla extending to below middle of the eye; lower jaw projecting beyond upper jaw; opercle with three flat spines, the upper two spines well developed. Scales ctenoid; small scales at the bases of dorsal, anal and pectoral fins. Preopercle margin coarsely serrate, developed spines near angle. The first two dorsal-fin spines shortest. No distinct notch between dorsal spines and soft rays but soft rays slightly elevated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,222,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">
Color (
<figureCitation box="[283,353,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1021,1045]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,417,998]" captionTargetId="figure-131@10.[151,1437,417,998]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Serranus novemcinctus, SAIAB 188950 (116.3âˆ’262.0 mm SL), from Walters Shoal, southern Madagascar, photograph by Allan D. Connell (NRF-SAIAB)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705500/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Brownish with nine dark vertical bars dorsally on body, the first four below the spinous dorsal fin; the next three under the soft dorsal rays, the eighth on the caudal peduncle and the last at the caudal-fin base; diagonal bar on the preopercle, originating behind the eye to margin of opercle at mid-pectoral fin position. Ventral body white. No spots on the fins but dorsal fin membranes may have some irregular bluish lines on basal third of fin membrane.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705500" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5705500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705500/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" startId="10.[151,250,1021,1045]" targetBox="[151,1437,417,998]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1021,1081]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1021,1045]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority=", SAIAB" authorityName="SAIAB" box="[293,628,1021,1045]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Serranus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="novemcinctus">
<emphasis box="[293,541,1021,1045]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Serranus novemcinctus,</emphasis>
SAIAB
</taxonomicName>
188950 (116.3âˆ’262.0 mm SL), from Walters Shoal, southern Madagascar, photograph by Allan D. Connell (NRF-SAIAB).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1127,1261]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,1127,1153]" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">Color in preservation.</emphasis>
Specimens lose color in preservation but the pattern, 
<emphasis box="[1056,1090,1128,1153]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="109">i.e.</emphasis>
nine vertical bars on body, and diagonal bar on the preopercle, remains visible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="109" type="distribution">
